comment._content: [http://www.flickr.com/photos/27331537@N06]  The NSW (O) 60-class entered service between October 1874 and January 1875. Built in England by Stephenson's and erected locally by Mort and Company, Sydney.  No 64 entered service in December 1874 and was withdrawn in 1889 having travelled 593,023 miles in the service of the state.
